		<div class="visual">
			<h4>Visual Learning</h4>
			<p class="style_paragraph">Visual learners prefer using images, pictures, colors and maps to organize information and communicate with others. They can visualize objects, plans and outcomes in their mind’s eye, and have a good spatial sense. Visual learners enjoy using white boards, love drawing, scribbling and doodling, and especially appreciate colors. 
</br></br>Ideal learning techniques for visual learners utilizes pictures, colors and other visual media. Children who are visual learners tend to enjoy activities centered on cutting, paper, crafting, and bright colors. 
</br></br>Picture or word based games particularly appeal to visual learners and provide optimized learning outcomes.</p>
