			<h4>Auditory Learning</h4>
			<p class="style_paragraph">Auditory learners like working with sound and music. They have good senses of pitch and rhythm and typically can sing, play a musical instrument, or identify the sounds of different instruments. Music invokes strong emotions for auditory learners, and they often notice the music playing in the background of movies and other media. </br></br>Ideal learning techniques for auditory learners utilizes sounds, rhyming and music in additional to visual association. Children who are auditory learners tend to enjoy activities centered around music and singing.</br></br>Word and story based games appeal to auditory learners and help provide optimized learning outcomes.</p>
