			<h4>Kinesthetic Learning</h4>
			<p class="style_paragraph">Kinesthetic learners learn best through touching and interacting with the world around them. They often like sports, exercise and other physical activities, and would rather learn and process information while doing something active. Kinesthetic learners are more sensitive to the world around them and notice textures and body language more readily than others. 
<br></br>Ideal learning techniques for kinesthetic learners includes physical work and activities utilizing touch and action. They respond well to acting out scenarios, writing and drawing, and flashcards.
<br></br>Action and story based games appeal to kinesthetic learners, and help engage these children for optimized learning outcomes.</p>
